cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of cross-domain face recognition using computer vision algorithms, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a guidance sub-network to ensure that the encoded visible-features contain more semantically meaningful information, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the optimization of an identity loss combined with the perceptual loss to achieve photo-realistic property while preserving discriminative characteristics, which is a common topic in graphics (cs.GR).
